message: Always use 'stove' on raw proteins and vegetables first; they typically become value 20. For grains (like rice, wheat, tortilla), use 'water' to soak them first, then use 'stove' on the 'soaked' grain to make it value 20. The highest value items (60) are created by combining exactly two cooked components: either (cooked protein + cooked vegetable) or (cooked protein + cooked soaked grain). Be careful: combining three or more items, especially already complex dishes, almost always results in an 'overcomplicated' item with a significantly reduced value of 20.
